
[1]corrosion

   CORROSION, n. s as z. From corrode. The action of eating or wearing
   away by slow degrees, as by the action of acids on metals, by which the
   substance is gradually changed. This is effected by the affinity of the
   menstruum with the component parts of the substance, in consequence of
   which the two substances unite and form new combinations.
